Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["\<\
What Makes Wolfram QuantumFramework Unique: A Verified Showcase\
\>", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"400bccce-4afd-4f21-8b73-b2aa03ba7db2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Wolfram QuantumFramework is a quantum laboratory built into the Wolfram \
Language. The objects of quantum theory, states, operators, channels, \
measurements, circuits, are exact symbolic expressions: they carry free \
parameters, compose with one another in closed form, and answer questions \
about themselves through one uniform interface. A computation here typically \
ends in a formula, the propagator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["U", "TI"], "(", 
   StyleBox["t", "TI"], ")"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "1c3c6985-02f8-45ff-a784-f096a1bd8736"],
 " of a time-dependent Hamiltonian, an optimization landscape you can \
differentiate, an entanglement entropy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["S", "TI"], "(", 
   StyleBox["t", "TI"], ")"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "bf323ed3-b8d1-4ee2-9e09-2d1d72ac8149"],
 " you can solve, rather than a table of numbers. The same objects run in any \
finite dimension, qubits, qutrits, spin-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["j", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "37e617a5-9bd1-466f-9eb2-8651ba765b52"],
 " multiplets, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["N", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "79ed8c75-3d0c-4e06-a085-e3ddfb364136"],
 "-level systems, and they reach outward as well, to OpenQASM, to device \
transpilation, to real quantum hardware. Its natural habitat is the \
computation whose deliverable is insight: a closed form, an exact threshold, \
a verified physical statement."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"759eaec0-a908-47a5-a257-cb3e9bf3d266"],

Cell["\<\
This document makes that concrete as five claims, each developed through \
worked examples:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"323853ce-0e9e-4de7-9723-ea46bf15210e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Symbolic-first, exact algebra by default.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Time-dependent Hamiltonians solved to closed-form propagators, a control \
Hamiltonian recovered from a target evolution, an exact QAOA landscape, a \
many-body entanglement entropy as a formula in time."
}], "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"6e4c4bb9-ada8-47eb-a00f-3af05e43f2a6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["One object model spans all of quantum theory.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Channels, POVMs, bosonic Fock space, and phase-space quasi-probabilities \
are the same kind of object as a gate, a master equation solves symbolically \
for every state and rate at once, and a thousand-qubit stabilizer state is \
one more object; the model stores the basis on every object, runs in any \
finite dimension, and closes with a full state-tomography loop."
}], "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"4051c6cd-1a56-4da1-a9f1-00ef5ff5bab9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["A quantum object is an ordinary Wolfram Language expression.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Built-ins like ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Plot"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "4ab9f686-35e4-4546-904b-6429ce7dc50b"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Reduce"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "13f855b0-ba86-4e77-b1ed-8f8134f830a8"],
 " apply to it directly, precisely because nothing about it is special."
}], "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"94370d9b-877d-4b05-affe-f422c0958e80"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Every object draws itself.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Bloch spheres, amplitude charts that carry the phases, measurement \
histograms, circuit diagrams, and the tensor network behind a circuit, each a \
one-call property of the object it depicts."
}], "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"8d8150ca-79da-4dd5-86e8-c0ae384daa5a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Open, inspectable, and an interoperability hub.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " The simulation engine's contraction order exposed as an option; OpenQASM \
in and out natively; transpilation to a device target; submission to a real \
QPU, with IBM as the worked example."
}], "ItemNumbered",ExpressionUUID->"399ad9bd-fe51-43dd-8f90-79b9c40ff1f1"],

Cell["\<\
The claims build on one another, symbolic objects at the base and real \
hardware at the summit, so we begin with the algebra everything else inherits.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"782c3ffa-8ac4-4c8d-b088-a340cafd8c25"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Claim 1: Symbolic-first, exact algebra by default", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3ddce9ba-adac-423a-b924-b9b5783f9b3e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Key feature:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " symbolic algebra pervades the ",
 StyleBox["whole", "TI"],
 " object model, not one function. The building blocks you reach for, a ",
 StyleBox["state",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "217bf09e-ade2-4050-9f45-a806eef27adf"],
 "), a ",
 StyleBox["Hamiltonian",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumOperator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "b57f7c5e-6f4e-4cf2-84c0-639e915b65a3"],
 "), its ",
 StyleBox["time evolution",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumEvolve"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "3e5b55fa-7e76-40c1-bdff-4f184afc825b"],
 "), and a ",
 StyleBox["circuit",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumCircuitOperator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "4597fb89-c495-4b65-a08e-063672ca58e7"],
 "), are each fully symbolic, and they compose into exact closed-form \
results. We take them in that order, starting with the simplest: a state \
whose amplitudes are symbols."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"468e026a-d67a-4fef-a795-f46523da720e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["A symbolic state", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"0332ffba-34f5-458f-b4ad-1995f2532ecd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "A ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumState"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "3875c2f3-8869-4a43-9562-86c90968e851"],
 " can carry free symbols. Build one with symbolic amplitudes and read them \
back:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9a1311b0-6f3e-4682-8b06-67bce9e27998"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psi", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumState", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Cos", "[", "\[Alpha]", "]"}], ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "\[Alpha]", "]"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{"Exp", "[", 
        RowBox[{"I", " ", "\[Beta]"}], "]"}]}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"psi", "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
  "Normal"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[172]:=",ExpressionUUID->"e1d955d9-3353-44bf-a22a-d946c29bf156"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Cos", "[", "\[Alpha]", "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
     RowBox[{"\[ImaginaryI]", " ", "\[Beta]"}]], " ", 
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "\[Alpha]", "]"}]}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.990277174423266*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[173]=",
 CellID->2113221836,ExpressionUUID->"ca2efee0-d5e6-4891-b987-955bc26b41fc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The amplitudes return exactly as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     StyleBox["cos",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
     StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"]}], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], " ", 
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["e", "TI"], 
     StyleBox[
      RowBox[{"i", "\[Beta]"}], "TI"]], 
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
    StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"]}], "}"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "b1474fac-e58e-4c31-9c39-52f97293c665"],
 ", symbols intact."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c9985533-f027-4e20-bfd3-c00c6ec537a3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The same object reports its exact Bloch geometry (",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "ComplexExpand"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "75703259-4e79-47e8-8b04-6678a4fa8613"],
 " treats ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "c9e99885-c89e-4449-9c45-4b112dcf70ba"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Beta]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "04fdda8e-98be-4f68-9938-e9ba4e8d1f3f"],
 " as real):"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5fc5f28d-9cfc-4c67-81f2-eec334a8189a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"psi", "[", "\"\<BlochVector\>\"", "]"}], " ", "//", " ", 
   "ComplexExpand"}], " ", "//", " ", "FullSimplify"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[174]:=",ExpressionUUID->"fbd2a0a1-5cce-44d5-a9de-82e54900a43a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Cos", "[", "\[Beta]", "]"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
     RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Alpha]"}], "]"}]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
     RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Alpha]"}], "]"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "\[Beta]", "]"}]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
    RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Alpha]"}], "]"}]}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9902771767416553`*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[174]=",
 CellID->559118126,ExpressionUUID->"e93c9bcf-2fb2-4244-94d0-c6d056c1ffe0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The Bloch vector returns exactly as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["(",
      Magnification->1.2], 
     StyleBox["sin",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", "2", 
     StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"], " ", 
     StyleBox["cos",
      FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
     StyleBox["\[Beta]", "TI"]}], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], " ", 
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", "2", 
    StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"], " ", 
    StyleBox["sin",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", 
    StyleBox["\[Beta]", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], " ", 
    StyleBox["cos",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "\[ThinSpace]", "2", 
    StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"]}], 
   StyleBox[")",
    Magnification->1.2]}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "711cd075-6b46-4960-aa6d-cb506ccad288"],
 ": the full geometry as functions of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Alpha]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a2c5f590-7779-44e5-be50-b64fcbab4159"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Beta]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "ec71a69a-add1-4d05-8c04-2d01743379c5"],
 ", without committing to numbers."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c19b5c1c-18f0-48fb-b435-b1012770f84f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["A time-dependent symbolic Hamiltonian", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"425d6167-e9f4-4d3d-947b-83d3b72ad2dc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Hamiltonians need not be static. The following is a spin-",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FractionBox["1", "2"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "92481330-717b-4765-88da-5b755b8d91e9"],
 " in a magnetic field that ",
 StyleBox["rotates",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " in the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"x", "y"}], "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "4153fe16-808e-4a14-8cde-05a90b9373cc"],
 "-plane at frequency ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["\[Omega]", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "16036853-828f-4ac2-bb96-4293d888a13a"],
 ", on top of a static ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["z", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "efc9134b-fc4e-4541-8f84-85066f98810b"],
 "-field, the standard model of magnetic resonance and of a driven qubit. It \
is ",
 StyleBox["explicitly time-dependent",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[FormalT]"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "c774bffe-1a56-4f6d-b879-1e84c5cccefe"],
 " is QF's time variable, and it appears inside the operator."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"78a952c2-bd35-4502-b163-371b6f76dd0f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"H", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Omega]0", "/", "2"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Z\>\"", "]"}]}], " ", "+", "\n", 
   "    ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[CapitalOmega]", "/", "2"}], " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Cos", "[", 
        RowBox[{"\[Omega]", " ", "\[FormalT]"}], "]"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<X\>\"", "]"}]}], " ", "+", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
        RowBox[{"\[Omega]", " ", "\[FormalT]"}], "]"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "\"\<Y\>\"", "]"}]}]}], 
     ")"}]}]}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9902771830992937`*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "In[176]:=",ExpressionUUID->"b29921e0-052d-4234-ba1c-f917c712ec12"],

