Cell["\<\
The tree is the engine's execution plan: the leaves are the circuit's gate \
and state tensors, every internal node is one pairwise contraction, and the \
dimension labels trace the intermediate sizes the greedy choice keeps small, \
exactly the quantity a good path minimizes and a bad one lets blow up.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8fc97873-e619-45e0-b799-fcce8fe8d7a2"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Export to OpenQASM 3.0 (native, no Python)", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"9f465f60-6e06-4d35-a2d7-344082ad7496"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumQASM"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "cea1458b-8845-4a10-aec3-507571731389"],
 " turns a circuit into the standard text format read by Qiskit, Cirq, and \
most hardware stacks."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8bfcf312-302e-4c66-a157-04967869f6da"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"QuantumQASM", "[", 
  RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<GHZ\>\"", "[", "3", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[316]:=",ExpressionUUID->"e833946b-05bc-4f38-9e4b-376ebecf1b8b"],

Cell[BoxData["\<\"OPENQASM 3.0;\\nqubit[3] q;\\nbit[0] \
c;\\nU(1.5707963267948966, 0., 3.141592653589793) q[0];\\nctrl(1) @ \
negctrl(0) @ U(3.141592653589793, 0., 3.141592653589793) q[0] q[1];\\nctrl(1) \
@ negctrl(0) @ U(3.141592653589793, 0., 3.141592653589793) q[1] q[2];\"\>"], \
"Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.990278189696932*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[316]=",
 CellID->1630139113,ExpressionUUID->"ebaf6d69-3db4-4ca3-9f69-21000eaf8c3f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The output is a complete OpenQASM 3.0 program: a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"qubit", "[", "3", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "8192e019-8124-4e37-8ae1-4ed68b525c8b"],
 " register, a Hadamard on ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"q", "[", "0", "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "08543513-192b-40ac-adae-6f8de2dcc87c"],
 " written as a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "U"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"cf33a724-e9ec-4a2e-95f0-51971050a1e8"],
 " rotation, and the two CNOTs as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"ctrl", " ", "@", " ", "U"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "4e7deb38-a59e-4a6f-8312-4b16b169dbc3"],
 " gates. The native emitter writes OpenQASM 3.0, and the importer below \
reads OpenQASM 2.0 or 3.0 alike. A 2.0 ",
 StyleBox["dump", "TI"],
 " is one option away through the qiskit path, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"QuantumQASM", "[", 
   RowBox[{"qc", ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<Version\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "2"}]}], "]"}]], 
  "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"a5ab1c22-bd28-4621-9de6-d58d26e83692"],
 " (that route needs Python; the 3.0 export and all imports do not). Export \
needs concrete angles: a circuit with a symbolic parameter returns a ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Failure"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "09142700-be6e-4914-be66-f5c2a9229117"],
 " rather than a QASM string, so resolve parameters to numbers at this \
boundary while keeping them symbolic everywhere else in QF (Claims 1 and 3)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1e9fe77e-1af4-4150-acfe-275689cb2bdd"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Import foreign OpenQASM and compute with it (native, no Python)\
\>", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"9b2b049f-c73f-4924-8795-2c4c83af34ad"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The same door runs the other way: hand ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QuantumCircuitOperator"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "15162402-4813-4439-932d-3f244ec71250"],
 " an OpenQASM string authored anywhere and get back a QF circuit, parsed in \
pure WL, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "reset"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "655acb60-83ed-4a68-abe7-314adf9f89ca"],
 ", controlled gates, mid-circuit ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "measure"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "b61a2a84-48a1-4c57-9898-fbc277e3c396"],
 " and all. Import a four-qubit circuit that runs the optimal quantum \
strategy for the CHSH game:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"16b992f9-b3e2-43ef-9ff4-bbae60df8b29"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"qc", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{
   "QuantumCircuitOperator", 
    "[", "\"\<OPENQASM 3.0;\nqubit[4] q;\nbit[4] c;\nreset q[0];\nreset q[3];\
\nU(1.5707963267948966, 0., 3.141592653589793) q[3];\nU(1.5707963267948966, \
0., 3.141592653589793) q[0];\nswap q[0] q[3];\nctrl(0) @ negctrl(1) @ \
U(1.5707963267948966, 3.141592653589793, 3.141592653589793) q[0] q[3];\n\
ctrl(1) @ negctrl(0) @ U(1.5707963267948966, 0., 0.) q[0] q[3];\nreset q[1];\n\
U(1.5707963267948966, 0., 3.141592653589793) q[1];\nreset q[2];\n\
U(1.5707963267948966, 0., 3.141592653589793) q[2];\nU(0., 0., 0.) q[0];\n\
ctrl(1) @ negctrl(0) @ U(1.5707963267948966, 0., 3.141592653589793) q[1] \
q[0];\nU(0.7853981633974483, 0., 0.) q[3];\nctrl(0) @ negctrl(1) @ \
U(1.5707963267948966, 0., 3.141592653589793) q[2] q[3];\nc[0] = measure q[0];\
\nc[1] = measure q[1];\nc[2] = measure q[2];\nc[3] = measure q[3];\>\"", 
    "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[317]:=",ExpressionUUID->"b87eac7b-abb8-4a45-b329-18828a8b8d57"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Once imported it is an ordinary QF object. Read its joint measurement \
distribution, label the four outcomes ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"(", 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["a", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
    StyleBox["x", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
    StyleBox["y", "TI"], 
    RowBox[{",", "\[ThinSpace]"}], 
    StyleBox["b", "TI"]}], ")"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "0979ee13-6b33-4b1f-8a56-e6c997717d60"],
 ", and ask Wolfram Language for the CHSH winning probability ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["Pr",
   FontSlant->"Plain"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "e1622873-ea3f-47fe-b08f-54244c72242b"],
 " in one line:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bed0c397-83f5-42dd-9500-3577e81ba5cb"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"NProbability", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"BitAnd", "[", 
     RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "y"}], "]"}], " ", "==", " ", 
    RowBox[{"BitXor", "[", 
     RowBox[{"a", ",", " ", "b"}], "]"}]}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"a", ",", " ", "x", ",", " ", "y", ",", " ", "b"}], "}"}], " ", "\[Distributed]",
     " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"qc", "[", "]"}], "[", "\"\<MultivariateDistribution\>\"", 
     "]"}]}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[318]:=",ExpressionUUID->"450298c0-3beb-49ad-ba10-fc0a5a067b64"],

Cell[BoxData["0.8535533905932738`"], "Output",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.990278195542528*^9},
 CellLabel->"Out[318]=",
 CellID->1783558073,ExpressionUUID->"849e5d33-5282-43ce-bd68-68f2c31d4e5f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The answer is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"0.8536", "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["cos",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], "\[ThinSpace]", "(", 
   RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "8"}], ")", "=", 
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"2", "+", 
     SqrtBox["2"]}], "4"]}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "7c2467de-7f7a-45cd-870a-7b36bd49d597"],
 ", exactly the ",
 StyleBox["Tsirelson bound",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", the quantum maximum for CHSH. A circuit authored in another tool became a \
probability distribution we query with native WL statistics."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d1da0c1b-3a5c-426a-bf4b-3abf5da260a7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["A hardware-aware transpilation target", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"663ec375-631e-4d19-a885-4c0805570c0d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
 "QiskitTarget"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "a1429b4c-e59f-431a-a0a6-ecd20d9268dd"],
 " carries a device spec (qubit count, native gate set, connectivity), \
validated at construction against qiskit's own ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "Target"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "2f4d7faf-8f88-45b9-888b-b9fcaf13f7c3"],
 " schema through the Python bridge. Build a 5-qubit linear-chain device and \
read its coupling map back:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"753c0e23-b1d2-46f3-853c-c3c149b25cdb"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"target", " ", "=", " ", 
