Cell[TextData[{
 "The exact bars are ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FractionBox["1", "2"]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "2873dc5a-5107-49ff-a041-b164151cb270"],
 " at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "000"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "00793f24-39ff-45f3-827a-139e773e877c"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "111"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "d3298d02-b0fa-4413-bdcb-5649173f25fa"],
 " and zero elsewhere; the device returned ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "0.428"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "8ae3592b-cd33-44dc-a468-3dbbaa71224d"],
 " at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "000"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "37d09f3c-ec5d-4401-a790-5adb6825f89f"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "0.420"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "c8924d10-88bc-4290-9e8d-d21568da0027"],
 " at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "111"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "86604f22-59ed-4457-82ff-5566baadf030"],
 ", with the remaining ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"15", "%"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "9a32c44d-3f4f-414f-92e0-9cf336d2da68"],
 " spread thinly over the six bitstrings the exact state forbids. That gap, \
read bar by bar off one figure, ",
 StyleBox["is", "TI"],
 " the device noise."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bf959e0e-406a-4e1f-998b-e05ec236f5cf"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Where This Leaves Us", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"03e431d8-13db-4952-bcb1-46f52773debf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Five claims, each cashed out in executed code. Symbolic algebra carried \
dynamics to closed form: the Rabi propagator of a rotating drive, a \
Landau-Zener sweep expressed in parabolic cylinder functions, a control \
Hamiltonian recovered exactly from its target evolution, a QAOA landscape \
whose maximum provably equals the true cut, the entanglement entropy of a \
quench as a function of time. One object model held the rest of the theory: \
channels, POVMs, Fock space, and phase space; a master equation solved once \
for every initial state and every rate, with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T", "TI"], "2"], "\[LessEqual]", "2", 
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["T", "TI"], "1"]}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "545e42e3-eee5-485c-99e0-5b9c1a9d3c99"],
 " arriving as a theorem rather than a remembered rule; a basis and a \
dimension on every object; a thousand-qubit stabilizer state with an exact \
half-chain entropy of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "496"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "8dc38a2c-7432-4faf-a7be-0afacb50fc1d"],
 " ebits; a state reconstructed from measured counts at fidelity ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "0.99998"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "e70e0906-aa1d-4b3a-827c-531bbce12a17"],
 ". Because these objects are ordinary Wolfram Language expressions, the \
language computed with them directly, and each of them drew itself. And the \
same objects left the system: out to OpenQASM and back, through a transpiler \
to a device's native gates, and onto a physical quantum processor, whose ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "4096"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "aa6d4e89-fc7d-49c2-a584-1e5f053617c7"],
 "-shot histogram stands in this document next to the exact distribution it \
approximates."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"04df6501-f4e6-4e13-adab-d8406000786e"],

Cell["\<\
Behind all five claims is one mechanism: quantum objects that are exact \
symbolic expressions compose, with each other and with the entire language. \
The distance from writing a Hamiltonian to reading its closed form, or to \
running it on hardware, is a handful of composable calls. A result that is a \
formula can be differentiated, reduced, or pushed to a limit; a result that \
is a circuit is already in the format the rest of the quantum ecosystem \
speaks.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9f3c2655-37bb-4af0-82af-c50f9890eea0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The next steps are the reader's: change the graph under the QAOA section, \
raise the spin past ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "1"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->"8b67070c-203e-4317-b43f-2a6326674a5b"],
 ", swap damping for dephasing, point the last section at a different \
backend. The document re-derives itself."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4cb0cbfe-575a-488a-af7b-0e0dafc4520c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Setup.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " Evaluate once before the cells:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cc27950f-c0a6-4715-baaf-be26873d5a94"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\>\"", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
  "Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`QuantumFramework`SecondQuantization`\>\"", "]"}],
   ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Needs", "[", "\"\<Wolfram`TensorNetworks`\>\"", "]"}], 
  ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[75]:= ",ExpressionUUID->"a80abfd6-601d-4561-855b-e4d68850b900"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Every cell was executed as shown (Wolfram Language 15.0, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"Wolfram", "/", "QuantumFramework"}]], "InlineFormula",
  ExpressionUUID->"cb0034bd-452b-48e9-98ea-0b437f957bf1"],
 " 2.0.0) and every stated output is the captured result, including the \
hardware run on ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "ibm_fez"], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "e8979590-1ed9-4a6a-8baf-a8a1737261ee"],
 "; reproducing the transpilation cells needs a Python installation with \
qiskit, and the hardware cells an IBM Quantum account."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ca5a2c1d-f7fc-4f50-92cc-d6039ee9865e"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
